Source:
C Programming for Everybody - RS-1: Produce output

Question:
Write a C program to produce the same output as this Python program using the %d and %s features of the printf() function.

Python Code:
print('Hello world')
print('Answer', 19)
print('Name', 'Sarah')

C Code:
#include <stdio.h>

main() {
    printf("Hello world\n");
    printf("Answer %d\n", 19);
    printf("Name %s\n", "Sarah");
}

Input:
N/A

Output:
Hello world
Answer 19
Name Sarah

Notes:
- Single quotes ‘ ’ are single characters 
- Double quotes “ ” are character arrays 
- %d -> corresponds to a number then converts to a string 
- %s -> corresponds to a string then converts to a string 
- $.1f -> print floating point number with one precision 
- \n to break to next line 

