Source:
C Programming for Everybody - RS-2: Read Input

Question:
Write a C program equivalent to this Python program

Python Code:
print('Enter US Floor')
usf = int(input())
euf = usf - 1
print('EU Floor', euf)

C Code:
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int usf, euf;

    printf("Enter US Floor\n");
    scanf("%d", &usf);
    euf = usf - 1;
    printf("EU Floor %d\n", euf);
}

Input:
2

Output:
Enter US Floor
EU Floor 1

Notes:
- scanf() is similar to input() 
- & -> call by reference for integers or floats 

