Source:
C Programming for Everybody - RS-3: Input / Output

Question:
Write a C program equivalent to this Python program

Python Code:
print('Enter name')
name = input()
print('Hello', name)

C Code:
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    char name[100];

    printf("Enter name\n");
    scanf("%100s", name);
    printf("Hello %s\n", name);
}

Input:
Sarah

Output:
Enter name
Hello Sarah

Notes:
- Predeclare a character array “char name[100]” and specify how long 
- scanf() for strings doesn’t require an ampersand &, but requires %s or %d, and can have a limit on it 

