Source:
C Programming for Everybody - RS-8: Write a Guessing Game

Question:
Write a C program to play a guessing game with the user that is equivalent to the Python program below. 
Your program should use a while loop and multi-way branch if (i.e. use else if).

Python Code:
while True:
    try:
        line = input()
    except:  # If we get EOF
        break
    line = line.strip()
    guess = int(line)
    if guess == 42:
        print('Nice work!')
        break
    elif guess < 42 :
        print('Too low - guess again')
    else :
        print('Too high - guess again')

C Code:
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int guess;

    while(scanf("%d", &guess) != EOF) {
        if ( guess == 42 ) {
            printf("Nice work!\n");
            break;
        }
        else if ( guess < 42 ) {
            printf("Too low - guess again\n");
        }
        else {
            printf("Too high - guess again\n");
        }
    }
}    

Input:
5
50
42

Output:
Too low - guess again
Too high - guess again
Nice work!

Notes:
N/A

