C Programming for Everybody - 1-3: Fahrenheit / Celsius with Header

Question:
Modify the temperature conversion program to print a heading above the table. 
Check the sample output for the required format of the heading.

Python Code:
N/A

C Code:
#include <stdio.h>

int main() { /* Fahrenheit-Celsius table */
    int fahr;
    char x[15] = "FAHR   CELSIUS";
    char y[15] = "===============";

    printf("%s\n", x);
    printf("%s\n", y);

    for (fahr = 0; fahr <= 300.0; fahr = fahr + 40.0) {
        printf("%4d %6.1f\n", fahr, (5.0/9.0)*(fahr-32.0));
    }
}

Input:
N/A

Output:
FAHR   CELSIUS
===============
   0  -17.8
  40    4.4
  80   26.7
 120   48.9
 160   71.1
 200   93.3
 240  115.6
 280  137.8

Notes:
N/A

