C Programming for Everybody - 1-10: Print words

Question:
Write a program which prints the words in its input, one per line. 
A word is any string separated by a space or newline.

Python Code:
N/A

C Code:
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int c;

    while ((c = getchar()) != EOF) {
         if (c == ' ') {
             printf("\n");
         }
         else {
             putchar(c);
         }
    }
}

Input:
But soft what light
through yonder window
breaks

Output:
But
soft
what
light
through
yonder
window
breaks

